race.comment: Looks an open race on paper. MEG'S MAGIC (13) looks well-placed back to this class after three runs back. She held her ground in a race dominated on the speed last start. She may have to concede a bigger start from the wide barrier here but if the track is suiting run-on horses by this stage of the day, she can be finishing over the top of them. On the other hand, VALLENCOURT (6) can put herself on the speed and take some catching, especially with the claim. She looks suited back to 1200m and she looks a big danger. STARTIDE (8) is mixing her form but if she can reproduce the run in similar class two starts back, she's an obvious top three chance. REINE OF NINE (15) might be ready to improve into the placings, while ONE KIND (1) keeps racing well and deserves plenty of thought for quaddies and exotics.
